Core changes that don't have three +1's yet, or have a veto.  (If you
make the threshold vote on one of these items, please move it to the
section for approved changes.)

    * r8292 (fix for Issue #1695)
      Fix a nasty bug in the 'changes' table reading code that caused
      in invalid set of changes to be returned.  This bug *probably*
      only gets triggered by cvs2svn during directory pruning, but
      cvs2svn is only gonna get more popular as time goes on...
      Notes: ghudson (ugly and a source of O(n^2) behavior, but better
                      than being incorrect, I guess)
      Votes:
       +1: cmpilato, kfogel, ghudson

       
    * r8299
      Fix a small bug in ra_dav's get_repos_root() implementation that caused
      it to return an incomplete root URL, if the session URL was already the
      root URL.
      Votes:
       +1: jszakmeister, ghudson


    * r8341, r8352
      Fix some more 'access denied' errors on Windows.
      Votes:
       +1: ghudson


    * r8346
      Fix infinite recursion in libsvn_subr/utf.c.
      Votes:
       +1: epg, ghudson

    * Issue #1705
      Exorcise apr_off_t.
      Justification: It's a big headache we want to get rid of
      now.  Creates crashes with the perl bindings.
      Notes: breser (I'd vote for this but I don't think my
                     vote counts).
             ghudson (svn_io_file_seek needs a little more work)
      Votes:
       +0: ghudson

    * r8296
      Change to correctly build Fedora Core 1 RPMs.
      Justification: Without this the generated package name
         contains "Unknown" instead of the platform abbreviation.
      Notes:
      Votes:
       +1: david, ghudson

    * r8368
      The subversion SWIG bindings now require swig-1.3.19.
      Justification: Without this the compile and RPM build breaks.
      Votes:
       +1: david

Core changes that already have three +1 votes and no vetos.  (If you
veto something below, or remove a threshold vote, please move it to
the section for unapproved changes.)

