These changes are to Subversion bindings.  Many are dependent on
specific "core" changes in the previous section, so we're planning to
finalize this list (and its votes) after we know the core changes,
that is, after Thursday, Jan. 8th 2004.

Bindings changes that affect the build system:

    * r8279, r8280 and r8318
     Fix the build system for building against separate apr-util.
     See Issue #1666
     Justification: Shouldn't require in tree apr or apache.
     Votes:
      +1: breser (for 8280, concept +1 for 8279)
      +1: mbk, epg, kfogel

    * r8290
     Applying r8279 + r8290 for javahl
     Breaks bindings if base is applied, javahl local change, low risk.
     Votes:
      +1: patrick (if above is applied)
      +1 (concept): kfogel

    * Issue #1690
     Support SWIG 1.3.20 and newer.
     Justification: An increasingly common version of SWIG that we need
                    to support.
     Votes:
      +1: breser, clkao
     
Bindings changes that don't affect the build system:

     * r8344
     Fix perl bindings to work with new date format. 
     Justification: Perl bindings won't even build now without this.
     Votes:
      +1: breser, epg, clkao

     * r8348
     Don't assume an int is the same size as a long in perl bindings.
     Justification: Prevent potential bizarre breakage on 64-bit platforms.
     And make blame work right when/if the apr_off_t thing gets handled
     on 32-bit platforms.
     Votes:
      +1: breser, clkao

-*- -*- -*- -*- -*- -*- -*- -*- -*- -*- -*- -*- -*- -*- -*- -*- -*- -*-

These changes are to Subversion tools that do not use the bindings.
As such, they may be updated independently of any "core" or API
changes.

    * r8357, r8364
      Make svn_load_dirs.pl printed output easier to use.
      Add default answers to yes no questions.
      Justification: Improve display, ease of use, low risk.
      Votes:
       +1: blair

    * r8366
      In svn_add_diffs.pl, change regex to match new r\d+ revision
      format from 'svn log'.
      Justification: Broken without fix, one line change.
      Votes:
       +1: blair
